The paper presents a visual analytics tool for optimizing crop planning decisions, which involves decision-making under uncertainty and analyzing large amounts of data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
